<s> The Doc_891494_288_302_Disease was probably an idiosyncratic and not toxic or allergic reaction. </s>
<s> In fact the concentration of free Doc_891494_403_406_Chemical was normal, the patient presented a retarded morbilliform Doc_891494_465_469_Disease during Doc_891494_477_480_Chemical treatment, the protidogram was normal, and an intradermic Doc_891494_539_542_Chemical injection had no local effect. </s>
<s> The authors conclude that in a patient starting Doc_891494_622_625_Chemical treatment an unexpected increase in Doc_891494_662_670_Disease, with EEG and mental changes occurring simultaneously, should alert the physician to the possible need for eliminating Doc_891494_790_793_Chemical from the therapeutic regimen, even if plasma concentrations are low. </s>
